HOUSE BILL DRH10037-ML-16
Short Title: Protect Those Who Serve & Protect Act of 2025. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Hastings.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT ENACTING THE PROTECT THOSE WHO SERVE AND PROTECT ACT OF 2025.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. This act shall be known as the "Protect Those Who Serve and Protect
5 Act of 2025."
6 SECTION 2. Article 8 of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
7 a new section to read:
8 "§ 14-34.7A. Assault on a public safety officer, law enforcement agency animal, or search
9 and rescue animal by throwing, spraying, or otherwise projecting water or other
10 substances.
11 (a) Definition. – The following definitions apply in this section:
12 (1) Law enforcement agency animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
13 (2) Public safety officer. – Any of the following:
14 a. A law enforcement officer.
15 b. A probation or parole officer.
16 c. A person who is employed at (i) a detention facility, as defined in
17 G.S. 143B-805, or (ii) any other detention facility operated under the
18 jurisdiction of the State or a local government.
19 d. A firefighter or rescue squad worker.
20 e. An emergency medical services personnel, as defined in
21 G.S. 131E-155.
22 f. A hospital employee, medical practice employee, licensed health care
23 provider, individual under contract to provide services at a hospital or
24 medical practice, hospital security personnel, or other emergency
25 health care provider not otherwise covered under sub-subdivision e. of
26 this subdivision.
27 g. A member of the North Carolina National Guard.
28 h. A member of any branch of the Armed Forces of the United States.
29 i. A juvenile court counselor or chief court counselor, as those terms are
30 defined in G.S. 143B-805.
31 j. An employee or volunteer at a school, as those terms are defined in
32 subdivision (6) of subsection (c) of G.S. 14-33.
33 (3) Search and rescue animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
34 (b) Offense and Punishment. – Unless covered under some other provision of law
35 providing greater punishment, a person is guilty of a Class I felony if the person commits an
