1 assault or battery on either of the following by throwing, spraying, or otherwise projecting, or
2 causing to be thrown, sprayed, or otherwise projected, water or any other substance at:
3 (1) A public safety officer (i) while the public safety officer is discharging or
4 attempting to discharge his or her official duties or (ii) because of the victim's
5 status as a public safety officer.
6 (2) A law enforcement agency animal or a search and rescue animal (i) while the
7 animal is in the performance of its duty or (ii) because of the animal's status
8 as a law enforcement agency animal or search and rescue animal."
9 SECTION 3. G.S. 14-34.8 reads as rewritten:
10 "§ 14-34.8. Criminal use of laser device.
11 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
12 (1) Laser. – Light amplification by stimulated emission of radiation.
13 (2) Law enforcement agency animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
14 (3) Public safety officer. – As defined in G.S. 14-34.7A.
15 (4) Search and rescue animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
16 (b) It is unlawful to intentionally point a laser device while the device is emitting a laser
17 beam at:
18 (1) Any of the following A public safety officer (i) while the person is in the
19 performance of his or her duties:duties or (ii) because of the person's status as
20 a public safety officer.
21 a. A law enforcement officer.
22 b. A probation or parole officer.
23 c. A person whose employment duties include the custody,
24 transportation, or management of persons who are detained or
25 confined to a detention facility, youth development center, or
26 correctional institution operated under the jurisdiction of the State or
27 a local government.
28 d. A firefighter.
29 e. An emergency medical technician or other emergency health care
30 provider.
31 f. A member of the North Carolina National Guard.
32 g. A member of any branch of the Armed Forces of the United States.
33 h. Court counselors whose employment duties include intake, probation,
34 post-release supervision, and court supervision services of juveniles.
35 (2) The head or face of any person not covered under subdivision (1) of this
36 subsection.
37 (3) A law enforcement agency animal or a search and rescue animal (i) while the
38 animal is in the performance of its duty.duty or (ii) because of the animal's
39 status as a law enforcement agency animal or search and rescue animal.
40 …."
41 SECTION 4. G.S. 14-32 reads as rewritten:
42 "§ 14-32. Felonious assault with deadly weapon with intent to kill or inflicting serious
43 injury; punishments.
44 …
45 (d) Any Unless covered under some other provision of law providing greater punishment,
46 any person who assaults an emergency worker a public safety officer with a deadly weapon and
47 inflicts serious injury shall be punished as a Class D felon.
48 (e) Any Unless covered under some other provision of law providing greater punishment,
